  e. Charge for services, hosting, compute, and resource access built on
     top of this software.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITIONS
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1. Format Openness

   Any software that reads, writes, or processes the .dejavue/ on-disk
   format (timeline.jsonl, decisions.md, state.md, handoff.md, references/)
   must remain interoperable with the canonical format specification
   published in this repository. You may not use technical measures, patent
   claims, contractual restrictions, or any other mechanism to prevent third
   parties from implementing the .dejavue/ format or building tools that
   consume it without depending on this software.

2. Identity Sovereignty

   You may not modify this software to prevent users from:

     a. Exporting all memory artifacts (.dejavue/ directory) in full at any
        time, without charge or delay.
     b. Migrating their memory to a different compatible tool or service.
     c. Using memory artifacts without this software (the format is the
        open contract, not the CLI).

3. Data Portability

   Any hosted service operating this software must, upon a user's written
   request, provide a complete machine-readable export of all memory data
   associated with that user's repositories within 30 days, at no charge.

4. No Lock-in

   You may not enforce any patent, trade secret, license term, or contractual
   restriction that would prevent a third party from:

     a. Implementing the .dejavue/ format specification.
     b. Building software that reads or writes .dejavue/ data.
     c. Forking this software and operating an independent service.

5. CLI Free Tier

   The local command-line interface (dejavue CLI) must remain available at
   no charge. Monetization may apply to hosted services, capsule deployments,
   and API access — but the core local tool must always be freely usable.

6. Attribution

   All distributions must retain this license notice. Hosted services and
   user-visible documentation must credit the Dejavue project and its
   contributors. Attribution in the lineage record (foundry.toml) is permanent
   and survives stewardship transitions.

7. Patent Non-Aggression

   Any contributor who holds patents that would be infringed by a conforming
   implementation of the .dejavue/ format specification grants a royalty-free,
   perpetual, irrevocable patent license to all parties for such implementation.

8. Source Availability for Network Services

   If you operate a publicly accessible service that uses a modified version
   of this software, you must make the complete corresponding source of your
   modifications available to users of that service under the terms of this
   license.

